For millions of South Africans mini-bus taxis are their only means of transport. • Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. Watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - For millions of South Africans, mini-bus taxis are their only means of transport. COVID-19 has made the idea of riding a taxi or visiting a rank a very scary thought. Social distancing is virtually impossible. READ: What should you do if you think you have COVID-19? Taxi association governing body, Santaco, will announce measures to be put in place to contain coronavirus inside taxis and at ranks. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. Four millions of South Africans mini-bus taxis are their only means of transport. Courtesy #DStv403